                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d698">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-30T19:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 30, 1935—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 30—2:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>107. Reference Embassy’s 101, October 29, noon. Following telegram has been
                    received from Yunnanfu: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“October 29, 3 p.m. Referring to Hankow’s October 26, noon. Provincial
                            Government believes that the situation is not serious. Tatsienlu
                            garrisoned by more than 10,000 Hunan and Szechwan troops. Red objective
                            is believed to be Sichang and Anning valley.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Nanking, Hankow.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
